      • newTracingDataRowIdFromCell

        public static GenericTable.TracingData newTracingDataRowIdFromCell(int columnOffset,
                                                                   java.lang.String regexForRowId,
                                                                   TraceabilityManagerHumanReadable.RowLevelPrefix prependerForRowId,
                                                                   java.lang.String columnId,
                                                                   boolean onlyTraceIfContentIsOverridden)
        Static constructor for tracing data which has the form [A]n.B
        where
        n
        is a text from a column identified by columnOffset and regexForRowId
        A and B
        are user-definable, see below
        Parameters:
        columnOffset - relative offset of the cell containing the rowId (cell must be on the same row)
        regexForRowId - regex describing the actual rowId to be extracted from the cell referenced by columnOffset; regex must contain exactly one group
        prependerForRowId - text to prepend the rowId with (will be inserted for [A])
        columnId - raw columnId of this cell (will be inserted for B)
        onlyTraceIfContentIsOverridden - if true this cell will only have tracing data attached if there is also override data for it
        Returns:
        a new instance of this class
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one of the arguments is malformed

      • newTracingDataFixedColumnIdConditional

        public static GenericTable.TracingData newTracingDataFixedColumnIdConditional(java.lang.String columnId,
                                                                              java.lang.String cellContentOfTargetCell,
                                                                              int targetCellOffset)
        Static constructor for tracing data with a stock row-part and a user-definable column-appendix (i.e. [r][3].myBeautifulColumnDescriptor) which will only be applied if a cell in the same row (specified by offset) matches a given pattern
        Parameters:
        columnId - arbitrary string to be used for the column part of the tracestring
        cellContentOfTargetCell - pattern of the cell to match
        targetCellOffset - offset of cellContentOfTargetCell with respect to the current cell (positive values mean further right, negative values further left, 0 is the same cell)
        Returns:
        a new instance of this class
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one of the arguments is malformed
        See Also:
        newTracingDataFixedColumnIdConditional(String, String)
